  "title": "2018 AMC 10B Problems/Problem 20",
  "problem": "A function $f$ is defined recursively by $f(1)=f(2)=1$ and \\[f(n)=f(n-1)-f(n-2)+n\\] for all integers $n \\geq 3$ . What is $f(2018)$ ? $\\textbf{(A) } 2016 \\qquad \\textbf{(B) } 2017 \\qquad \\textbf{(C) } 2018 \\qquad \\textbf{(D) } 2019 \\qquad \\textbf{(E) } 2020$",
  "solution": "For all integers $n \\geq 7,$ note that \\begin{align*} f(n)&=f(n-1)-f(n-2)+n \\\\ &=[f(n-2)-f(n-3)+n-1]-f(n-2)+n \\\\ &=-f(n-3)+2n-1 \\\\ &=-[f(n-4)-f(n-5)+n-3]+2n-1 \\\\ &=-f(n-4)+f(n-5)+n+2 \\\\ &=-[f(n-5)-f(n-6)+n-4]+f(n-5)+n+2 \\\\ &=f(n-6)+6. \\end{align*} It follows that \\begin{align*} f(2018)&=f(2012)+6 \\\\ &=f(2006)+12 \\\\ &=f(2000)+18 \\\\ & \\ \\vdots \\\\ &=f(2018-6\\cdot336)+6\\cdot336 \\\\ &=f(2)+2016 \\\\ &=\\boxed{\\textbf{(B) } 2017}. \\end{align*} ~MRENTHUSIASM",
